[Nouns] underestimation; depreciation (detraction) [more]; pessimism, pessimist; undervaluing; modesty [more].
[Verbs] underrate, underestimate, undervalue, underreckon; depreciate; disparage (detract) [more]; not do justice to; misprize, disprize; ridicule [more]; slight (despise) [more]; neglect [more]; slur over.
make light of, make little of, make nothing of, make no account of; belittle; minimize, think nothing of; set no store by, set at naught; shake off as dewdrops from the lion's mane.
[Adjectives] depreciating, depreciated; unvalued, unprized.
